article.linkText: Gittens scores 20, Florida International defeats Houston Christian 83-74
article.story: HOUSTON -- — Dashon Gittens scored 20 points as Florida International beat Houston Christian 83-74 on Wednesday night. Gittens had eight rebounds and five assists for the Panthers (1-3). Arturo Dean added 18 points while shooting 7 of 11 from the field and 3 for 6 from the line, and he also had six assists and six steals. Petar Krivokapic was 4 of 9 shooting, including 3 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 2 for 3 from the line to finish with 13 points. Pierce Bazil led the way for the Huskies (0-2) with 16 points and two steals. Bruce Carpenter added 15 points for Houston Christian. In addition, Michael Imariagbe had 14 points and four blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
